Key Match Events: Travis Head and Matthew Short cut loose in the powerplay, scoring 62 runs off the next four overs.
Brydon Carse removed Travis Head and Matthew Short, but Australia managed to stay ahead despite losing a couple of wickets.
Brydon Carse bowled Matthew Short for a 23-ball maiden ODI fifty.
Josh Inglis pulled consecutive sixes off Carse in the 20th over, putting pressure on England's spinners.
Adam Zampa induced a collapse in England's innings, taking key scalps of Ben Duckett and Jacob Bethell.
Harry Brook scored seven sixes in his innings, but was eventually dismissed for 119.
Pre-Game Insights: Phil Salt set the tone in the opening over with three boundaries off Mitchell Starc and two plays and misses.
Australia's tactics involved using 23 consecutive overs of spin and 28 off the last 29 in total.
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Duckett capped a strong series with a fine century.
England's innings fell apart after Harry Brook fell to Zampa, leading to a collapse of 107 for 8.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The rain arrived during the interval and returned four balls after a result had been assured with a DLS of 116 for 2.
Australia maintained their unbeaten World Cup record against England.
